value.value: A sex cord-stromal tumor arising from the ovary, without metastatic potential.

label.value: Lacrimal Gland Carcinoma ex Pleomorphic Adenoma

value.value: A carcinoma arising in a pre-existing pleomorphic adenoma in the lacrimal gland.

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Neoplasm in the Pituitary Gland

value.value: A malignant neoplasm metastasizing to the pituitary gland from another anatomic site.  The vast majority are carcinomas usually arising from the breast, lung, and gastrointestinal tract.
A benign neoplasm arising from the dermis. It is characterized by the presence of neoplastic fibroblasts without malignant characteristics.

A neoplasm that arises from the external ear and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential. Representative examples include ceruminous adenoma, polyp, and lipoma.

label.value: Dermoid Cyst of the Spinal Cord

value.value: A dermoid cyst that arises from the spinal cord.

A WHO Grade 1 astrocytoma which arises in the cerebellum.  The tumor is composed of spindle shaped cells with numerous collections of reddish astrocytic fibers called Rosenthal fibers. Over 80% or the cerebellar astrocytomas of childhood are pilocytic. Pilocytic astrocytomas may rarely occur in adults. They are usually treated by surgical resection and in most cases have a favorable prognosis.
Any agent that binds to or interferes with binding to any of the opioid receptor subtypes, thereby blocking the actions of opioid agonists.
A lymphoma that arises from the testis and is not associated with lymphoma in another anatomic site.
A verrucous carcinoma that arises from the plantar aspect of the foot.

An extragonadal malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the mediastinum. It is characterized by the presence of uniform cells with clear or eosinophilic cytoplasm, round nucleus with one or more nucleoli, and distinct cellular borders.  It usually arises from the anterior mediastinum.  It may present with respiratory distress, chest pain, or superior vena cava syndrome or it may be asymptomatic, with the tumor detected on routine chest x-ray.  The prognosis of mediastinal pure seminomas is favorable compared to the mediastinal non-seminomatous malignant germ cell tumors.

A usually aggressive invasive adenocarcinoma of the prostate gland composed of large glands containing tall columnar cells.  The columnar cells have abundant cytoplasm and are reminiscent of endometrial carcinoma.  This type of adenocarcinoma has a tendency to metastasize to the lung and penis.

A poorly circumscribed, intermediate fibrocytic neoplasm arising from the superficial soft tissues. It is characterized by the presence of spindle-shaped fibroblasts, and an infiltrative growth pattern.
A hamartoma that occurs in the spinal cord.

An enediyne antineoplastic antibiotic hybrid containing an aminoglycoside chromophore.  Zinostatin is isolated from the bacterium Streptomyces carzinostaticus.  The aminoglycoside component of zinostatin intercalates into DNA and the benzene diradical intermediate of the enediyne core binds to the minor groove of DNA, resulting in single- and double-strand breaks in DNA and apoptosis. (NCI04)

A pancreatic intraepithelial neoplasia characterized by the presence of tall columnar cells that form flat or papillary, micropapillary, and basally pseudostratified architectural patterns.  Mild cytological atypia is present.

Interchanges of genetic material among different chromosomes following the breaking off of pieces of chromosomes such that the total chromosome composition may still contain all of the genetic material.Balanced Chromosomal Rearrangement.

Interchanges of genetic material among different chromosomes following the breaking off of pieces of chromosomes such that the total chromosome composition does not contain all of the genetic material.
An irregularity in the number of chromosomes.
A salt or ester of mineral iodine. Iodide salts are mild reducing agents and many react with oxygen to give iodine.
